          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Granting Release And Compassion Effectively Act of 2018 or the GRACE Act</b></p> <p>The bill amends the Second Chance Act of 2007 to modify provisions that authorize the Bureau of Prisons (BOP) to reduce the prison term (i.e., release early) certain federal prisoners.</p> <p>Specifically, in the case of a defendant diagnosed with a terminal illness, the bill requires the BOP to comply with new requirements. Among other things, the BOP must </p> <ul> <li>notify the defendant's representatives of the terminal illness and opportunity to request a reduced sentence, and </li> <li>allow family members to visit the defendant.</li> </ul>]]></text>
          <updateDate>2018-02-28T05:00:00Z</updateDate>
